      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/developer-resources/forum/developers/alljoyn-firefox-os" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  <div class="field-comment-body view-mode-full">
    <p>Hi Sqahmad,</p><p>I am not famliar with the firefox OS platform, but in a nutshell you are correct.  You will need to run the routing node software (legacy daemon software) in the firefox OS.  You may be able to leverage the bundled router approach in which the application you compile contains the software, but the environment will need to be able to run both javascript and c++ software.</p><p>One of the benefits of AllJoyn being open source software is that you do have the ability to tinker around and hopefully enlist others to help in the effort.</p><p>Let us know how this goes,</p><p>Brian Spencer</p>  </div>
      </div>

      
