        <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/developer-resources/forum/developers/alljoyn-firefox-os" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  <div class="field-comment-body view-mode-full">
    <p>Hi Brian, Thanks for your reply.</p><p>    Firefox OS platform is based on linux, derived from android project. So here's what I did so far.</p><p>  I have built firefox OS from source. Then I built alljoyn for android using firefox OS build as android_source. In alljoyn I built alljoyn core and JS bindings (libnpalljoyn.so). JS bindings use Gecko SDK, and Firefox OS is also based on gecko which lies between user space and OS space. </p><p>  When I test alljoyn-daemon binary and rawservice and rawclient on FFOS phone using adb shell, it works. </p><p>   I have installed sample JS apps (simple service and client) in FFOS phone. I have also adb pushed libnpalljoyn.so in /system/lib folder where all other shared libraries are stored. JS application doesn't load libnpalljoyn.so, although it loads other libraries when I check it using ./run-gdb command and attaching it to SimpleService app. </p><p> Does any one have any idea of what could be missing here. Any pointers will be helpful. Thanks.</p>  </div>
      </div>

      
