      <div class="forum-post-content">
        <span rel="sioc:reply_of" resource="/developer-resources/forum/developers/alljoyn-firefox-os" class="rdf-meta element-hidden"></span>
  <div class="field-comment-body view-mode-full">
    <p>Hi Sqahmad,</p><p>I'm again, not familiar with Firefox OS to best describe how to do this.  My assumption would be to see if there is a way to load up a C++ library. Otherwise you will need to make changes to the Firefox OS itself to make this happen, IE create a new Web API that can load up and use the AllJoyn C++ code.  The Javascript APIs do not allow for the creation of a UDP packet and to send out a multicast packet, so you will encounter issues porting over the entire C++ engine to Javascript.</p><p>-Brian Spencer</p>  </div>
      </div>

      
