    <p>Hello</p><p>I need some expert advice on the following options:</p><p>1. Alljoyn daemon listens on tcp port, so can we do something like installing a daemon binary on the device, and use javascript to access the daemon over tcp?. It looks similar to how AJTC is implemented?. OR what about considering FFOS device as  a thin client and porting only thin client part of the code to Javascript?.  </p><p>2. Another point that comes to mind is, is it possible (and how) to run Alljoyn daemon behind a web service?. This way a regular javascript app would be able to access the daemon and use alljoyn service? </p><p><span>Thanks</span></p><p>Syed</p>  </div>
